Key Match Events: Nick Castellanos hit a two-run homer in the first inning and scored the winning run in the sixth.
Zack Wheeler allowed two runs on four hits and three walks in six innings, striking out nine.
Weston Wilson’s swinging bunt single in the sixth inning scored Castellanos from third to give the Phillies the lead.
Aramis Garcia tagged out a runner at the plate in the fourth and later threw out a runner at second who represented the potential tying run in the ninth.
Post-Match Reflections: Nick Castellanos expressed satisfaction with the team's collective contributions despite missing key players.
Phillies manager Rob Thomson emphasized the importance of continuing to perform well until the division title is officially clinched.
Zack Wheeler reflected on his performance, acknowledging it was a battle but expressing comfort with his current form.
José Alvarado discussed his recent resurgence and focus on competing without worrying about uncontrollable factors.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillies played without Alec Bohm and J.T. Realmuto for the entire series and without Kyle Schwarber for more than half the series.
The Phillies have an eight-game lead over the Mets in the NL East with 16 games to play and could clinch their first division title soon.
José Alvarado has pitched five scoreless innings in five appearances since returning from handling a personal matter in Venezuela.
